{"key":"post-10270457","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10270457</id>\n<content>The overpressure plug on a canner does not seal below 0 PSI, thus they don't hold a vacuum.&amp;nbsp; You'd need to replace the nozzle and weight with a toggle valve, and replace the blowout plug with one made for a sterilizer.&amp;nbsp; However, that only leaves you with one means of overpressure protection.&amp;nbsp; Sterilizers have two: A blowout plug and a spring actuated relief valve, thus they're safer.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10270502</next>\n<prev>10270234</prev>\n<first>10270033</first>\n<last>10271065</last>\n<when>1241230200</when>\n<utime>05/02/09 05:10 AM</utime>\n</post>"}